wiki.content: According to the Who Gon Stop Me Songfacts, the origins of the song lay in a call from Bu Thiam, Def Jam's VP of A&R to R&B artist and producer Verse Simmonds, to submit tracks for Watch The Throne. Simmonds told MTV News he and his production partner immediately went to work. "What we did is, we locked in a week, we just went crazy on everything Jay and Kanye," he said. "I remember telling Sham, I was like, 'Yo, I think this dubstep stuff is going to be the next new flavor that everybody gotta be on. It gotta have a hip-hop feel to it still.'"
